<subsection xml:id="subsec-exclusive_events">
    <title>Exclusive Events</title>
        <p>
            Two or more events are mutually exclusive if they cannot happen at the same time.
        </p>
        <activity>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{Work in groups}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Roll a fair die once.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Event A: Getting an even number
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Event B: Getting an odd number
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                Discuss:
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Are these events mutually exclusive?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            what is <m>\textbf{P(even) + P(odd)?} </m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
           
        </activity>
        <p>  
            <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
        </p>

        <p>
            In other words, the occurrence of one event means the other cannot occur.
        </p>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A bag contains 3 red, 2 blue, and 1 yellow marble. One marble is drawn.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Find the probability of drawing:
                    <ol marker="a">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                A red marble
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                A yellow marble
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                A red or yellow marble
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    Total marbles <m>= 6</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m> \textbf{P(Red)} = \frac{3}{6} \textbf{and} \textbf{ P(Yellow)} = \frac{1}{6}</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Red and yellow are mutually exclusive (you can't pick both at once)
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \textbf{P(Red or Yellow)} </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \frac{3}{6} + \frac{1}{6} = \frac{4}{6} = \frac{2}{3}</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
     
</subsection>